      • radius

        double radius()
        Get the distance of this point from the origin (0,0)
        Returns:
        square root of (x^2 the y^2)

      • radians

        double radians()
        Get the radians of this coordinate in polar form. AKA angle formed between the line from (0,0) to this point, and the line extending from (0,0) through (1,0).

      • setStringPrecisionSig

        void setStringPrecisionSig(int sigfigs)
        Set the precision of the string representation through toString()
        Parameters:
        sigfigs - the number of significant figures to be output by toString()
        Preconditions
        sigfigs > 0
        Postconditions
        all calls to toString() after this, but before calling setStringPrecisionDec() will return coordinates with up to sigfigs number of significant figures

      • setSTringPrecisionDec

        void setSTringPrecisionDec(int decplaces)
        Set the precision of the string representation through toString()
        Parameters:
        decplaces - the number of places after the decimal point to be output by toString()
        Preconditions
        sigfigs >= 0
        Postconditions
        all calls to toString() after this, but before calling setStringPrecisionSig() will return coordinates with up to decplaces number of decimal places
